avelers, and as a book of omens. Today, it is regarded as the richest repository of ancient Chinese mythology and shamanistic wisdom. The Guideways may have been illustrated from the start, but the earliest surviving illustrations are woodblock engravings from a rare 1597 edition. Seventy-six of those plates are reproduced here for the first time, and they provide a fine example of the Chinese engraver's art during the late Ming dynasty. This beautiful volume, compiled by a well-known specialist in the field, provides a fascinating window on the thoughts and beliefs of an ancient people, and will delight specialists and general readers alike.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 07. Jul 2020) 4aancient chinese beliefs. 4aancient chinese myths. 4aancient chinese. 4aancient folklore. 4aancient mythology. 4aasian folklore. 4aasian mythology. 4achina guide. 4achinese book of omens. 4achinese fauna. 4achinese flora. 4achinese folklore. 4achinese geography. 4achinese literature. 4achinese mountains. 4achinese mythology. 4achinese shaman. 4achinese wisdom. 4afolklore. 4amedieval china. 4amythical creatures. 4amythology. 4awarring states china. 4awestern han dynasty. 7aART / Asian / General.2bisacsh1 aStrassberg, Richard E., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013z97831106904220 cprintz978052029851440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780520922785423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9780520922785.jpg  a978-3-11-069042-2  UC Press eBook Package Backlist 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aGBV-deGruyter-alles